              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-5c408c59-67bc-4aa9-b89c-3bd57945f424');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",

              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      try {\n",
              "        const charts = await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction(\n",

              "      }\n",

              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-66aa16fa-bd4e-4d2d-9a68-50e9995f1ee5');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

        "import json\n",
        "import re\n",
        "complete_dataset = \"arxiv/arxiv-metadata-oai-snapshot.json\"\n",
        "partial_dataset = \"./arxiv_bio.json\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Defines the CS category\n",
        "pattern = r\"(^|\\s)q-bio\\.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Filters the data with respect to the pattern and creates a new file\n",
        "with open(complete_dataset, 'r') as f_in, open(partial_dataset, 'w') as f_out:\n",
        "    for line in f_in:\n",
        "        entry = json.loads(line)\n",
        "        if re.search(pattern, entry[\"categories\"]):\n",
        "            json.dump(entry, f_out)\n",
        "            f_out.write('\\n')"

        "complete_dataset = \"arxiv/arxiv-metadata-oai-snapshot.json\"\n",
        "partial_dataset = \"./arxiv_bio.json\"\n",

        "# Defines the complete ArXiv-df\n",

        "\n",
        "# Defines the CS-ArXiv-df\n",
        "bio_arxiv_df = pd.read_json(partial_dataset, lines=True)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mciWKqvY1Wpw"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import requests\n",
        "from bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "url = \"https://arxiv.org/category_taxonomy\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Send a GET request to the URL\n",
        "response = requests.get(url)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get the page source from the response content\n",
        "page_source = response.text\n",
        "\n",
        "# Parse the page source\n",
        "soup = BeautifulSoup(page_source, 'html.parser')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Find the category list element\n",
        "category_list = soup.find(id='category_taxonomy_list')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract the category information\n",
        "categories = []\n",
        "main_category = None\n",
        "for category in category_list.find_all('h4'):\n",
        "    if category.find_previous('h2'):\n",
        "        main_category = category.find_previous('h2').text\n",
        "    category_id = category.text.split(' (')[0]  # Switched with 'category_name'\n",
        "    category_name = category.text.split('(')[1].split(')')[0]  # Switched with 'category_id'\n",
        "    category_description = category.find_next('p').text\n",
        "    categories.append({\n",
        "        \"ID\": category_id,  # Switched with 'category_name'\n",
        "        \"Main Category\": main_category,\n",
        "        \"Name\": category_name,  # Switched with 'category_id'\n",
        "        \"Description\": category_description\n",
        "    })\n",
        "# Create a dataframe from the categories list\n",
        "categories_df = pd.DataFrame(categories)\n",
        "#categories_df.set_index(\"ID\", inplace=True)\n",
        "categories_df"
      ],

              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-4fd4c9ad-a5fa-44c5-9241-f9711ffd5c6d');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "\n",
              "\n",

              "            style=\"display:none;\">\n",

              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-632fa530-a68f-49ec-821d-e06b95641151');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

              "        const charts = await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction(\n",
              "            'suggestCharts', [key], {});\n",
              "      } catch (error) {\n",
              "        console.error('Error during call to suggestCharts:', error);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.remove('colab-df-spinner');\n",
              "      quickchartButtonEl.classList.add('colab-df-quickchart-complete');\n",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import altair as alt\n",
        "\n",
        "category_counts = categories_df['Main Category'].value_counts().reset_index()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Rename the columns for clarity\n",
        "category_counts.columns = ['Main Category', 'Count']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate the percentage for each section\n",
        "category_counts['Percentage'] = (category_counts['Count'] / category_counts['Count'].sum()) * 100\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the pie chart using Altair\n",
        "chart = alt.Chart(category_counts).mark_arc().encode(\n",
        "    theta='Count:Q',\n",
        "    color=alt.Color('Main Category:N', legend=alt.Legend(title='Main Category')),\n",
        "    tooltip=['Main Category', 'Count', 'Percentage:Q'],\n",
        ").properties(\n",
        "    title='Main Category Distribution',\n",
        "    width=800,  # Adjust the width of the chart\n",
        "    height=500  # Adjust the height of the chart\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the chart\n",
        "chart.save(\"chart1.json\")\n",
        "chart"
      ],

              "<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n",
              "  var VEGA_DEBUG = (typeof VEGA_DEBUG == \"undefined\") ? {} : VEGA_DEBUG;\n",
              "  (function(spec, embedOpt){\n",
              "    let outputDiv = document.currentScript.previousElementSibling;\n",
              "    if (outputDiv.id !== \"altair-viz-ccad9b002ff34d87bfe9447bfeb17183\") {\n",
              "      outputDiv = document.getElementById(\"altair-viz-ccad9b002ff34d87bfe9447bfeb17183\");\n",
              "    }\n",
              "    const paths = {\n",
              "      \"vega\": \"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega@5?noext\",\n",
              "      \"vega-lib\": \"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega-lib?noext\",\n",
              "      \"vega-lite\": \"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega-lite@4.17.0?noext\",\n",
              "      \"vega-embed\": \"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm//vega-embed@6?noext\",\n",
              "    };\n",
              "\n",
              "    function maybeLoadScript(lib, version) {\n",
              "      var key = `${lib.replace(\"-\", \"\")}_version`;\n",
              "      return (VEGA_DEBUG[key] == version) ?\n",
              "        Promise.resolve(paths[lib]) :\n",
              "        new Promise(function(resolve, reject) {\n",
              "          var s = document.createElement('script');\n",
              "          document.getElementsByTagName(\"head\")[0].appendChild(s);\n",
              "          s.async = true;\n",
              "          s.onload = () => {\n",
              "            VEGA_DEBUG[key] = version;\n",
              "            return resolve(paths[lib]);\n",
              "          };\n",
              "          s.onerror = () => reject(`Error loading script: ${paths[lib]}`);\n",
              "          s.src = paths[lib];\n",
              "        });\n",
              "    }\n",
              "\n",
              "    function showError(err) {\n",
              "      outputDiv.innerHTML = `<div class=\"error\" style=\"color:red;\">${err}</div>`;\n",
              "      throw err;\n",
              "    }\n",
              "\n",
              "    function displayChart(vegaEmbed) {\n",
              "      vegaEmbed(outputDiv, spec, embedOpt)\n",
              "        .catch(err => showError(`Javascript Error: ${err.message}<br>This usually means there's a typo in your chart specification. See the javascript console for the full traceback.`));\n",
              "    }\n",
              "\n",
              "    if(typeof define === \"function\" && define.amd) {\n",
              "      requirejs.config({paths});\n",
              "      require([\"vega-embed\"], displayChart, err => showError(`Error loading script: ${err.message}`));\n",
              "    } else {\n",
              "      maybeLoadScript(\"vega\", \"5\")\n",
              "        .then(() => maybeLoadScript(\"vega-lite\", \"4.17.0\"))\n",
              "        .then(() => maybeLoadScript(\"vega-embed\", \"6\"))\n",
              "        .catch(showError)\n",
              "        .then(() => displayChart(vegaEmbed));\n",
              "    }\n",
              "  })({\"config\": {\"view\": {\"continuousWidth\": 400, \"continuousHeight\": 300}}, \"data\": {\"name\": \"data-ec6e141494b54c5ebd435f4f074b6394\"}, \"mark\": \"arc\", \"encoding\": {\"color\": {\"field\": \"Main Category\", \"legend\": {\"title\": \"Main Category\"}, \"type\": \"nominal\"}, \"theta\": {\"field\": \"Count\", \"type\": \"quantitative\"}, \"tooltip\": [{\"field\": \"Main Category\", \"type\": \"nominal\"}, {\"field\": \"Count\", \"type\": \"quantitative\"}, {\"field\": \"Percentage\", \"type\": \"quantitative\"}]}, \"height\": 500, \"title\": \"Main Category Distribution\", \"width\": 800, \"$schema\": \"https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v4.17.0.json\", \"datasets\": {\"data-ec6e141494b54c5ebd435f4f074b6394\": [{\"Main Category\": \"Physics\", \"Count\": 51, \"Percentage\": 32.903225806451616}, {\"Main Category\": \"Computer Science\", \"Count\": 40, \"Percentage\": 25.806451612903224}, {\"Main Category\": \"Mathematics\", \"Count\": 32, \"Percentage\": 20.64516129032258}, {\"Main Category\": \"Quantitative Biology\", \"Count\": 10, \"Percentage\": 6.451612903225806}, {\"Main Category\": \"Quantitative Finance\", \"Count\": 9, \"Percentage\": 5.806451612903226}, {\"Main Category\": \"Statistics\", \"Count\": 6, \"Percentage\": 3.870967741935484}, {\"Main Category\": \"Electrical Engineering and Systems Science\", \"Count\": 4, \"Percentage\": 2.5806451612903225}, {\"Main Category\": \"Economics\", \"Count\": 3, \"Percentage\": 1.935483870967742}]}}, {\"mode\": \"vega-lite\"});\n",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import altair as alt\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "partial_dataset = \"./arxiv_bio.json\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Defines the complete ArXiv-df\n",
        "#arxiv_df = pd.read_json(complete_dataset, lines=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Defines the CS-ArXiv-df\n",
        "bio_arxiv_df = pd.read_json(partial_dataset, lines=True)\n",
        "# Merge cs_arxiv_df with categories_df on 'categories' column\n",
        "merged_df = pd.merge(bio_arxiv_df, categories_df, left_on='categories', right_on='ID', how='left')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate the count of papers for each subcategory\n",
        "subcategory_counts = merged_df['Name'].value_counts().reset_index()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Rename the columns for clarity\n",
        "subcategory_counts.columns = ['Subcategory', 'Count']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Sort the subcategories by count in descending order\n",
        "subcategory_counts = subcategory_counts.sort_values('Count', ascending=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the bar chart using Altair\n",
        "chart = alt.Chart(subcategory_counts).mark_bar().encode(\n",
        "    x='Count:Q',\n",
        "    y=alt.Y('Subcategory:N', sort='-x'),\n",
        "    color=alt.Color('Subcategory:N', legend=alt.Legend(title='Subcategory'))\n",
        ").properties(\n",
        "    title='Number of Biology Papers by Subcategory',\n",
        "    width=800,  # Adjust the width of the chart\n",
        "    height=500  # Adjust the height of the chart\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the bar chart\n",
        "chart.save(\"chart2.json\")\n",
        "chart"
      ],

              "    }\n",

        "import altair as alt\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# Count the number of articles for each author\n",
        "author_counts = bio_arxiv_df['authors'].explode().value_counts()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Select the top 10 authors with the most publications\n",
        "top_authors = author_counts.head(10).reset_index()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Rename the columns for clarity\n",
        "top_authors.columns = ['Author', 'Publication Count']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create the bar chart using Altair\n",
        "chart = alt.Chart(top_authors).mark_bar().encode(\n",
        "    x=alt.X('Author:N', title='Author'),  # Treat the author as nominal data\n",
        "    y=alt.Y('Publication Count:Q', title='Number of Publications'),  # Treat the publication count as quantitative data\n",
        "    color=alt.Color('Author:N', scale=alt.Scale(scheme='category20'), legend=None)  # Assign different colors to each bar\n",
        ").properties(\n",
        "    title='Authors with the Most Publications (Computer Science)',\n",
        "    width=600,\n",
        "    height=400\n",
        ")\n",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import en_core_sci_lg  # model downloaded in previous step\n",
        "import spacy\n",
        "# Parser\n",
        "parser = nlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm', disable = ['ner', 'tagger'])\n",
        "parser.max_length = 7000000\n",
        "\n",
        "def spacy_tokenizer(sentence):\n",
        "    mytokens = parser(sentence)\n",
        "    mytokens = [ word.lemma_.lower().strip() if word.lemma_ != \"-PRON-\" else word.lower_ for word in mytokens ]\n",
        "    mytokens = [ word for word in mytokens if word not in stopwords and word not in punctuations ]\n",
        "    mytokens = \" \".join([i for i in mytokens])\n",
        "    return mytokens"
      ],
      "metadata": {

          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"

              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "# Assuming 'abstract' is the name of the column in filtered_df\n",
        "abstracts = filtered_df['processed_abstract']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create a TF-IDF Vectorizer\n",
        "vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Transform the abstracts into TF-IDF vectors\n",
        "tfidf_matrix = vectorizer.fit_transform(abstracts)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate cosine similarity matrix\n",
        "cosine_similarities = cosine_similarity(tfidf_matrix, tfidf_matrix)\n",
        "#print(cosine_similarities[-1])\n",
        "\n",
        "#print(cosine_similarities.shape)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get the shape of the array\n",
        "num_rows, num_columns = cosine_similarities.shape\n",
        "\n",
        "# Index of the last element in each row\n",
        "last_index = num_columns - 1\n",
        "\n",
        "# Iterate over rows and find the most similar element for each row\n",
        "for i in range(num_rows):\n",
        "    # Find the index of the most similar element in the row (excluding the last element)\n",
        "    most_similar_index = np.argmax(cosine_similarities[i, :last_index])\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get the actual value of the most similar element\n",
        "    most_similar_value = cosine_similarities[i, most_similar_index]\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"For row {i}, the most similar element (excluding the last element) is at index {most_similar_index} with similarity {most_similar_value}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "if(most_similar_value > 0.50):\n",
        "  print(\"Seems plagerised\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "  print(\"New document not seems to be plagerised. We will further be checking for generated text detection\")"
      ],
